(1567, 20, 'Writing Culture', 'N', 2011, 30985, 'N', 'Lecture', 'Primarily for Undergraduates', 'Expository Writing', 15, '', '', 'Our desires and perceptions take shape not just individually but through shared systems of meaning: culture. How can we see culture, though, when our own often seems transparently natural (like water to a fish, one anthropologist observed), and others'' intrinsically alien? Short answer: through encounter. With the aim of writing original cultural analysis of Harvard and other subjects, we''ll study anthropologists (Geertz, Rosaldo), social theorists (Williams, James), and other writers (McCarthy, Didion, Alexie).', '', ''),
