(1579, 20, 'Sound, Noise, Music', 'N', 2011, 52625, 'Y', 'Lecture', 'Primarily for Undergraduates', 'Expository Writing', 15, '', '', 'Music is everywhere around us-entangled with (and a part of) the many noises we experience. And yet we tend to think of music as distinct from other sounds, isolating it in our minds even when we can''t with our ears. In this course, we will question that isolation, and examine music as an aspect of its greater environment - natural, social, and technological-rather than apart from it.', '', ''),
