(1587, 20, 'Gothic Fiction', 'N', 2011, 51502, 'Y', 'Lecture', 'Primarily for Undergraduates', 'Expository Writing', 15, '', '', 'This course explores the meaning and function of Gothic literature, a genre characterized by secrecy, perversion, madness, and death. In our first unit, short stories-of various centuries and nations-will allow us to develop a working definition of Gothic. In unit two we''ll interpret Jane Austen''s Gothic spoof Northanger Abbey in the context of both popular fiction and eighteenth-century debates about reading. The third unit introduces research methods that focus on the works of Edgar Allan Poe.', '', ''),
