(1594, 20, 'The Ethics of Human Experimentation', 'N', 2011, 97946, 'Y', 'Lecture', 'Primarily for Undergraduates', 'Expository Writing', 15, '', '', 'To learn about human biology and behavior, researchers often use people as research subjects. Although such research has produced many social benefits, it sometimes comes at a cost to study participants. In this course, you will weigh the costs and benefits of a controversial psychological study, take a psychological approach to understanding why unethical research practices occur, and consider how research can be done to maximize its impact while minimizing the risks to human participants.', '', ''),
