(1625, 20, 'Contemporary Theatre', 'N', 2011, 23202, 'Y', 'Lecture', 'Primarily for Undergraduates', 'Expository Writing', 15, '', '', 'Since the 1950s, theatre has refused to shy away from controversial issues, provoking audiences to reconsider their beliefs and re-imagine the world. This course will grapple with the plays of influential and provocative playwrights from the past five decades, and debate issues of politics, ethics, race, and sexuality. Playwrights will include Harold Pinter, Tennessee Williams, Paula Vogel, Tony Kushner, Samuel Beckett, and Sarah Kane.', '', ''),
