(1646, 20, 'Art & the Nude', 'Y', 2011, 21317, 'Y', 'Lecture', 'Primarily for Undergraduates', 'Expository Writing', 15, '', '', 'This course explores how the representation of the nude in modern art broke with the past and fundamentally reshaped the cultural landscape of the nineteenth and twentieth centuries. Taught in conjunction with the "Degas and the Nude" exhibition at the Museum of Fine Arts, we first consider the tradition of the flawless goddess, how artists like Manet, Cezanne, Matisse and Picasso transgressed it, and, finally, how contemporary artists continue to radically transform the nude today.', '', ''),
