(3405, 205, 'Molecular Biology of the Auditory System', 'N', 2011, 211, 'N', 'Seminar', 'Primarily for Graduates', 'Pathology', 0, '', '', 'Advances in molecular biology of hearing. Transcriptional and post-translational regulation of inner ear development. Topics: exploration of genome identifying genes critical for inner ear function, inner ear stem cells and regenerative capacity in various species.', 'Introductory courses in neurobiology and molecular biology are recommended.', 'Given in alternate years.'),
(3406, 209, 'Tumor Pathophysiology and Transport Phenomena - A Systems Biology Approach', 'N', 2011, 5934, 'Y', 'Lecture', 'Primarily for Graduates', 'Pathology', 0, '', '', 'Tumor pathophysiology plays a central role in the growth, metastasis, detection, and treatment of solid tumors. Principles of transport phenomena are applied to develop a quantitative understanding of tumor biology and treatment.', '', 'Given in alternate years. Offered jointly with the Medical School as PA 712.0. Classes held at MIT.'),
