(4772, 219, 'Tibetan Religious Literature: Seminar', 'N', 2011, 9500, 'Y', 'Seminar', 'Primarily for Graduates', 'Tibetan', 0, '', '', 'The readings will be drawn from works on the moral life and the condition of auspiciousness, by Rong-zom Chos-bzang (11th century); Sa-skya Pandita (1182-1251); and Taranatha (1575-1634).', 'At least one previous year of classical Tibetan is required.', 'An intermediate to advanced reading class on Tibetan religious literature. Offered jointly with the Divinity School as 3831.'),
